Do the following two commands in R give the same output? [see_image_1] #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:04112021123050] https://t.co/JD1UuK0Dam

Correct Ans: No. Due to operator precedence, the two commands do not give same output. The first command is equivalent to `!(1+1)` and the second command is equivalent to `1+!1`. Also due to implicit coercion, in the first command, #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:04112021220018]

`!(1+1)` is converted to `FALSE` because of the last logical operation. In the second command `!1` is first converted to `FALSE` and then due to `+` converted back to `1`. Hence the first command gives the output `FALSE` and the #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:04112021220018]
second command gives the output `1`. [see_image_1] #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:04112021220018] https://t.co/df4NLqrtKz
